  "slug": "spaghetti-bolognaise",
  "title": "Spaghetti Bolognaise",
  "subtitle": "A pasta dish for any night of the week.",
  "excerpt": "Spaghetti Bolognaise. A weeknight pasta, sauce in one pan, pasta in another, finished together.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook. The bones of the recipe sit in the Italian home-cooking tradition documented by writers like Pellegrino Artusi (La Scienza in Cucina, 1891) and Marcella Hazan.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spaghetti Bolognaise. The dish belongs to the Italian home-cooking register: straightforward, ingredient-led, calm at the hob. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pasta in a pan, sauce in another. The trick is the meeting, the noodles finish in the sauce, holding the starchy water that binds the two.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
